The paper deals with tensor completion, which is a problem in signal processing and machine learning. The use of the tensor ring decomposition is a recent development in this area, and the paper proposes a new method for tensor completion based on this decomposition. The paper also provides a theoretical analysis of the proposed method, which involves a convex optimization program. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of signal processing and communication. The paper also involves machine learning and optimization, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively. The use of the tensor ring decomposition is a new development in tensor analysis, which is covered by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves experiments on synthetic and real-world data, which are covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
